sequenceDiagram
    %% Flow 1: TrustyAI Model Monitoring
    rect rgb(230, 245, 255)
    Note over Client,DB: Flow 1 — TrustyAI Model Monitoring
    participant Client as External Client
    participant Route as OpenShift Route<br/>443/TCP HTTPS<br/>TLS reencrypt
    participant OAuth as OAuth Proxy Sidecar<br/>8443/TCP HTTPS<br/>TLS (service-ca)
    participant TAS as TrustyAI Service<br/>8080/TCP HTTP
    participant KServeIS as KServe InferenceService
    participant DB as External Database<br/>JDBC TLS (optional)

    Client->>Route: HTTPS/443<br/>TLS edge→reencrypt
    Route->>OAuth: HTTPS/8443<br/>TLS (service-ca)<br/>OAuth token forwarding
    OAuth->>TAS: HTTP/8080<br/>localhost (no TLS)
    KServeIS->>TAS: HTTPS/443 (internal svc)<br/>TLS (service-ca)<br/>Inference payloads for monitoring
    TAS->>DB: JDBC (varies)<br/>TLS optional (db-ca cert)<br/>Username/password auth
    end

    %% Flow 2: LMEval Job Execution
    rect rgb(255, 245, 230)
    Note over User,Driver: Flow 2 — LMEval Job Execution
    participant User as User
    participant K8sAPI as Kubernetes API<br/>6443/TCP HTTPS
    participant Operator as TrustyAI Operator
    participant InitC as Init Container<br/>(ta-lmes-driver)
    participant LMEval as Main Container<br/>(lm-eval Python)
    participant Driver as Driver Sidecar<br/>18080/TCP HTTP
    participant HF as HuggingFace Hub<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant S3 as S3 Storage<br/>443/TCP HTTPS

    User->>K8sAPI: Create LMEvalJob CR<br/>HTTPS/6443<br/>Kubernetes RBAC
    K8sAPI-->>Operator: Watch event
    Operator->>K8sAPI: Create Pod<br/>HTTPS/6443<br/>ServiceAccount
    Note over InitC: Copies driver binary<br/>to shared EmptyDir volume
    InitC->>LMEval: Shared volume (filesystem)
    LMEval->>HF: HTTPS/443 (if online allowed)<br/>TLS 1.2+<br/>HF token (optional)
    LMEval->>S3: HTTPS/443 (if offline mode)<br/>TLS 1.2+<br/>AWS IAM credentials
    Operator->>Driver: POST /GetStatus<br/>HTTP/18080<br/>No auth (pod-local)
    Driver-->>Operator: Job status JSON<br/>(progress via tqdm parsing)
    end

    %% Flow 3: Guardrails Orchestration
    rect rgb(230, 255, 230)
    Note over Client2,DetectorIS: Flow 3 — Guardrails Orchestration
    participant Client2 as External Client
    participant GRoute as OpenShift Route<br/>443/TCP HTTPS<br/>TLS reencrypt
    participant GOAuth as OAuth Proxy (optional)<br/>8432/TCP HTTPS
    participant GORCH as Orchestrator<br/>8032/TCP HTTPS<br/>TLS (service-ca)
    participant GenIS as Generation<br/>InferenceService
    participant DetectorIS as Detector<br/>InferenceServices

    Client2->>GRoute: HTTPS/443<br/>TLS reencrypt
    GRoute->>GOAuth: HTTPS/8432<br/>TLS (service-ca)<br/>OAuth (optional)
    GOAuth->>GORCH: HTTPS/8032<br/>TLS (service-ca)
    GORCH->>GenIS: HTTPS (varies)<br/>TLS (service-ca)<br/>Passthrough Authorization header
    GORCH->>DetectorIS: HTTPS (varies)<br/>TLS (service-ca)<br/>Passthrough Authorization header

    Note over Client2,GORCH: Optional: Gateway sidecar on port 8090/8490
    end
